LINE.Text: In 2010, total UK overall primary energy consumption in
primary energy terms (i.e. fuels obtained directly from
natural sources) was 218.5 million tonnes of oil
equivalent, 3 per cent higher than in 2009. However, it
should be noted that in 2009 UK primary energy
consumption was at its lowest level in the last 20
years as a result of the downturn in the economy.
